    "comment": "Rationale: Mint1 regulates inhibitory transmission and Fig. 7 shows that Mint1 KO mice exhibit paired-pulse depression of IPSCs. This supports an impairment in the regulation of GABA release and release probability.\n\nSingle KO of Mint1 does not impair excitatory transmission as shown in Fig. 5 but the additionally referenced annotation demonstrates that Mint1 acts redundantly with Mint2 to control presynaptic release at excitatory synapses.. Experimental description: Mint1 KO mice were studied.",
